<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Male</emphasis>
(holotype). Total length 1.48; carapace 0.66 long, 0.59 wide; abdomen 0.80 long, 0.55 wide. Carapace circular, brownish, with dark brown marks laterally and brown median line on anterior half (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Merizocera ratnapura sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443260" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">34C</figureCitation>
). Fovea shallow. Thoracic region distinctly elevated medially. Clypeus and labium brown. Sternum dark brown. Abdomen slightly elongated, dark brown. Legs light brown; measurements: I, III and IV missing, II 5.74 (1.66, 0.24, 1.76, 1.41, 0.67). Palp (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 33" captionStartId="F33" captionText="Figure 33. Merizocera ratnapura sp. nov., holotype male. A Bulb, dorsal view B bulb, retrolateral view C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CO = conductor, CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure33" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443259" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">33A-D</figureCitation>
): femur slender, five times longer than patella; patella not swollen; tibia not swollen; tibia not swollen, 1/2 femur length; cymbium with distal protrusion, 1/3 femur length, length ratio of dorsal elongation and cymbium: 0.91; bulb pale yellow, pyriform with embolus and conductor arising distally; embolus elongated and bent, 2.5 times longer than bulb, gradually tapering and darkened at the tip; conductor basally connected with embolus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Female</emphasis>
(paratype). Similar to male in colouration and general features but slightly larger (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Merizocera ratnapura sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443260" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">34D, E</figureCitation>
). Measurements: total length 1.48; carapace 0.70 long, 0.62 wide; abdomen 0.76 long, 0.51 wide. Leg measurements: I 9.38 (2.59, 0.24, 2.97, 2.45, 1.13), II 6.75 (1.92, 0.24, 2.10, 1.66, 0.83), III 5.10 (1.47, 0.23, 1.53, 1.24, 0.63), IV 7.36 (2.08, 0.23, 2.35, 1.82, 0.88). Epigastric area (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Merizocera ratnapura sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443260" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">34B</figureCitation>
): dark brown elliptical patch. Endogyne (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 34" captionStartId="F34" captionText="Figure 34. Merizocera ratnapura sp. nov., holotype male and paratype female. A Endogyne, dorsal view B female epigastric area, ventral view C male habitus, dorsal view D female habitus, dorsal view E female habitus, ventral view. Abbreviation: SP = spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure34" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443260" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">34A</figureCitation>
) with a pair of widely tubular spermathecae, medially with stalked spermathecae bearing globose end.
</paragraph>
